{
  "stem": "19055.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] [SIGHS] slowly, slowly, the good food that the Americans provided us, the hope or the-- my, my parents help, I, I can become better and better.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] It's hard to believe, but by the time 1946 came in Hungary, my tuberculosis spontaneously cured itself.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "All my lesions were calcified.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I lived.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "That's one of the few or many miracles that happened during those times.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Those homes that we stayed, actually, just to, to clear my conscience some people had to leave their homes for me, even they were Germans, were for high-ranking German SS officers and their families, which were built that whole community by the Nazi government to, to put this people.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "We found the photographs of these people in their uniforms and, and Nazi reliquary everywhere, and Nazi flags, and medals, and whatnot.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "So my conscience is clear.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I think we deserved to be in those places.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were there during the summer, the whole summer.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of 1945-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] and [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] constant contact with the American troops.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one day, the Americans told us that they would had to leave the place-- this was the Elbe River area-- because according to the agreement, the Soviet troops will take over.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Americans will go back west.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We wanted to go home.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They wanted to go back to Hungary to, to see what happens, if our family is still there, or-- and we were curious.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Americans said, you could come with us if you wanted.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we chose to stay.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they lowered the American flag.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the Russian troops came in.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They raised the red flag.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And there was another strange uniform, which I have never seen before.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
